document_data.Trivia:
*[[Hell hound]]s' bodies smelled of smoke and sulfur.
*[[Iron golem]]s of [[Ironslag]] vented sulfurous smoke from their vents when activated.
*[[Kruthik]]s could not stand the smell of their dead. The creatures' insides reeked of sulfur. Kruthik ichor, innards, and body parts were a valuable commodity in the areas where these monstrous insects were common.{{Cite dragon/430/Ecology of the Kruthik}}
*[[Oblex]] could create duplicates of creatures that were virtually indistinguishable from the original apart from a faint odor of sulfur around them.
*[[Nightmare (creature)|Nightmares']] and [[red dragon]]s' breath of fire had a heavy distinct stench of sulfur.
*In addition, a red dragon's [[dung]] contained significant quantities of sulfur and [[potassium nitrate]].<ref>{{Cite dragon/134/The Ecology of the Red Dragon|36}}
*[[Saurial]]s of [[Tarkhaldale]] were known to exude the scent of brimstone when confused.{{cite dragon/292/Lords of the Lost Vale}}
